---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Launching the Ultraviolet Public Alpha">
  <article class="article-page">
    <header>
      <p class="eyebrow">Public alpha</p>
      <h1>Launching the Ultraviolet Public Alpha</h1>
      <p class="post-meta">Ultraviolet / Blacklight Foundation</p>
    </header>

    <p>
      Ultraviolet is an alpha systems programming language for generated code
      humans can still review. The language is designed around explicit
      semantics, local reasoning, one accepted source form where possible, and
      static-by-default behavior.
    </p>

    <p>
      Generated code is becoming infrastructure. It is reviewed in pull
      requests, debugged when systems fail, audited for security properties, and
      trusted in production paths. Ultraviolet asks what a systems language
      should look like when that review path is part of the design.
    </p>

    <p>
      The project currently has an alpha language specification and a functional
      bootstrap compiler. The next public work is moving the compiler and
      surrounding infrastructure into a buildable, documented public alpha with
      CI, examples, diagnostics, and generated-code demos.
    </p>

    <p>
      Blacklight Foundation is funding this work through three concrete goals:
      the $25,000 Public Alpha Launch Fund, the $35,000 Reviewable Codegen Demo
      Fund, and the $120,000/year Maintainer-in-Residence Fund. These funds
      support compiler migration, release infrastructure, documentation,
      examples, diagnostics, contributor onboarding, public reports, and a
      flagship generated-code demo.
    </p>

    <p>
      Companies and individuals interested in supporting the work can sponsor a
      founding tier or fund a public milestone. Sponsor conversations can start
      at
      <a href="mailto:sponsors@ultraviolet-lang.org">
        sponsors@ultraviolet-lang.org
      </a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
